table_description: The audit_checks table represents a record of regular checks performed on various sites to ensure compliance and adherence to standards. It stores information about the site being checked, the date of the check, the auditor who conducted the check, and the audit score obtained. This table is typically used in analytics and business workflows to track the performance of different sites over time and identify areas for improvement.
column_description: The audit_pk column represents a unique identifier for each audit check record, allowing for efficient retrieval and updating of individual records. It is an integer data type, indicating a whole number value. This column matters because it enables the tracking of individual audit checks and facilitates data analysis and reporting.
